%3E%20A%20group%20of%20over%20100%20literary%20translators%20signed%20a%20statement%20in%20solidarity%20with%20the%20people%20of%20Gaza%20on%20November13%2C%20calling%20for%20a%20ceasefire%20in%20Gaza%20and%20the%20end%20to%20the%20violence%20against%20Palestinians%20in%20the%20occupied%20West%20Bank.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20statement%2C%20organised%20by%20translators%20Anna%20Gunin%20and%20Maya%20Chhabra%2C%20addressed%20the%20connection%20translators%20had%20with%20writers%20from%20Gaza%2C%20despite%20the%20strip%20being%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ecut%20off%20from%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world%20by%20a%20constant%20blockade%20since%202007.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20Palestinians%20who%20live%20%5Bin%20Gaza%5D%20cannot%20leave%20without%20exit%20permits%20from%20Israel%20or%20Egypt%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20statement%20said.%20%E2%80%9CGaza%E2%80%99s%20airspace%20and%20sea%20border%20are%20both%20controlled%20by%20Israel.%20Yet%20writers%20from%20Gaza%20continue%20to%20reach%20out%20to%20tell%20the%20world%20what%20is%20happening%20to%20them.%20Sometimes%20they%20are%20killed%20just%20days%20or%20weeks%20after%20their%20words%20reach%20us.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20said%20the%20translators%20watch%20%E2%80%9Cin%20horror%20as%20Israeli%20bombs%20fall%20on%20Gaza%2C%E2%80%9D%20citing%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aljazeera.com%2Fnews%2Fliveblog%2F2023%2F11%2F13%2Fisrael-hamas-war-live-gazas-two-largest-hospitals-shut-amid-nonstop-raids%23%3A~%3Atext%3DMore%2520than%252011%252C200%2520Palestinians%2520have%2Cstands%2520at%2520more%2520than%25201%252C200.%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ecurrent%20death%20toll%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20the%20area%2C%20which%20now%20stands%20at%2011%2C200%20people.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CFaced%20with%20this%20carnage%2C%20the%20undersigned%20literary%20translators%20feel%20morally%20