er.com%2Faspen-institute-donors-supreme-court-justice-elena-kagan-brett-kavanaugh-scotus-ethics-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Emillionaire%20lawyers%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20exclusive%20events%2C%20all%20nine%20justices%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20said%20Monday%20that%20they%20had%20agreed%20to%20a%20code%20of%20ethics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20code%20is%20very%20similar%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.uscourts.gov%2Fjudges-judgeships%2Fcode-conduct-united-states-judges%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ecode%20of%20conduct%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20binds%20lower%20federal%20judges.%20The%20five%20canons%20have%20the%20same%20titles%2C%20and%20some%20passages%20are%20lifted%20verbatim%20from%20the%20other%20judges'%20code.%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20even%20noted%20the%20similarity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20there%20are%20several%20differences%20%E2%80%94%20and%20one%20is%20key.%20Other%20judges%20are%20told%2C%20%26quot%3BA%20judge%20shall%20disqualify%20himself%20or%20herself%20in%20a%20proceeding%20in%20which%20the%20judge's%20impartiality%20might%20reasonably%20be%20questioned.%26quot%3B%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20the%20new%20rule%20reads%3A%20%26quot%3BA%20Justice%20should%20disqualify%20himself%20or%20herself%20in%20a%20proceeding%20in%20which%20the%20Justice's%20impartiality%20might%20reasonably%20be%20questioned.%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BShould%2C%26quot%3B%20not%20%26quot%3Bshall.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20even%20if%20the%20word%20was%20%26quot%3Bshall%2C%26quot%3B%20there's%20still%20no%20recourse%20for%20those%20who%20may%20disagree%20with%20a%20Justice's%20decision%20to%20not%20recuse%20themself.%20If%20a%20member%20of%20the%20public%20wants%20to%20make%20a%20complaint%20about%20a%20federal%20judge%2C%20the%20law%20lays%20out%20how.%20But%20that%20law%2C%20the%20Judicial%20Conduct%20%26amp%3B%20Disability%20Act%2C%20doesn't%20define%20%26quot%3Bjudge%26quot%3B%20to%20include%20Supreme%20Court%20justices%2C%20partly%20over%20legal%20concerns%20that%20Congress%20can't%20tell%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20what%20to%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court's%20Code%20of%20Conduct%20doesn't%20have%20any%20enforcement%20mechanism%2C%20saying%20that%20the%20ethics%20rules%20are%20voluntary%20and%20rely%20on%20ethical%20self-regulation%20by%20the%20Justices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20the%20top%20court's%20critics%20were%20quick%20to%20seize%20on%20the%20differences%20between%20the%20rules%20for%20other%20judges%20and%20the%20new%20Supreme%20Court%20ethics%20code.%20%26quot%3BWithout%20a%20clear%20enforcement%20mechanism%2C%20this%20'code%20of%20conduct'%20is%20just%20a%20PR%20stunt%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20group%20Accountable.US%20said%20in%20an%20emailed%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsupreme-court-ethics-rules-missing-word-should-shall-2023-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699910517000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65528d11385143459e8c364c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsupreme-court-ethics-rules-missing-word-should-shall-2023-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22After%20years%20of%20scrutiny%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court's%209%20justices%20have%20agreed%20on%20an%20ethics%20code.%20But%20the%20wording%20is%20weak%20and%20there's%20no%20way%20to%20enforce%20the%20code.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Jack%20Newsham)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A89%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsupreme-court-ethics-rules-missing-word-should-shall-2023-11%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22US%20stamp%20sells%20for%20a%20record-breaking%20%242m%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699910103000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news