-over-next-year-global-ceo-123111300878_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Favaya-to-add-india-staff-strength-by-20-over-next-year-global-ceo-123111300878_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Citing%20the%20Israel-Hamas%20War%2C%20NSO%20Group%20Sought%20Urgent%20Meeting%20With%20Blinken%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F07%2F24204013%2FIMG_4150.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Israeli%20firm%2C%20NSO%20group%2C%20which%20is%20known%20for%20Pegasus%20spyware%20and%20blacklisted%20by%20Washington%2C%20has%20asked%20for%20a%20meeting%20with%20the%20US%20State%20Department%2C%20including%20Secretary%20of%20State%20Anthony%20Blinken%2C%20in%20connection%20with%20the%20ongoing%20Israel-Hamas%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftech%2Fus-entity-list-israeli-spyware-nso-group-pegasus-trade-blacklist-malicious-cyber-activities%5C%22%3ETwo%20years%20ago%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20US%20government%20added%20Israeli%20companies%2C%20NSO%20group%20and%20Candiru%20to%20the%20Commerce%20Department%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98entity%20list%E2%80%99%2C%20which%20is%20a%20federal%20blacklist%20that%20would%20restrict%20exports%20of%20US%20technology%20to%20the%20company.%20The%20move%20was%20dictated%20by%20%E2%80%9Cevidence%20that%20these%20entities%20developed%20and%20supplied%20spyware%20to%20foreign%20governments%20that%20used%20these%20tools%20to%20maliciously%20target%20government%20officials%2C%20journalists%2C%20businesspeople%2C%20activists%2C%20academics%2C%20and%20embassy%20workers%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20had%20been%20part%20of%20an%20international%20collaborative%20investigation%20known%20as%20%E2%80%98%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fproject-pegasus-journalists-ministers-activists-phones-spying%5C%22%3EPegasus%20Project%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%99%2C%20that%20tracked%20the%20leaked%20database%20of%20thousands%20of%20telephone%20numbers%20that%20were%20believed%20to%20have%20been%20listed%20by%20multiple%20government%20clients%20of%20NSO%20group.%20Comprising%2017%20news%20organisations%20in%2010%20countries%2C%20the%20Pegasus%20Project%20was%20coordinated%20by%20Forbidden%20Stories%20with%20technical%20support%20of%20Amnesty%20International.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20couple%20of%20months%20after%20being%20blacklisted%2C%20NSO%20group%20hired%20a%20law%20firm%2C%20Los%20Angeles-based%20Paul%20Hastings%20LLP%2C%20to%20conduct%20an%20active%20lobbying%20effort%20to%20get%20out%20of%20the%20entity%20list%20in%20January%202022.%20This%20was%20initially%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fnso-group-pegasus-lobbying-us-trade-blacklist%5C%22%3Ereported%20by%20%3Cem%3EProPublica%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20November%207%2C%20partner%20at%20Paul%20Hastings%2C%20Timothy%20Dickinson%2C%20sent%20a%20letter%20and%20an%20email%20to%20request%20an%20%E2%80%9Curgent%20meeting%E2%80%9D%20to%20the%20US%20State%20Department.%20The%20documents%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fefile.fara.gov%2Fdocs%2F6743-Informational-Materials-20231107-22.pdf%5C%22%3Epublicly%20filed%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20the%20Justice%20Department%20as%20part%20of%20the%20Foreign%20Agents%20Registration%20Act.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENSO%20Group%E2%80%99s%20latest%20action%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheintercept.com%2F2023%2F11%2F10%2Fnso-group-israel-gaza-blacklist%2F%5C%22%3Ereported%20first%20by%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Intercept%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20am%20writing%20on%20behalf%20of%20%5Bthe%5D%20NSO%20Group%20to%20urgently%20request%20an%20opportunity%20to%20engage%20with%20Secretary%20Blinken%20and%20the%20officials%20at%20the%20State%20Department%20regarding%20the%20importance%20of%20cyber%20intelligence%20technology%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20the%20grave%20security%20threats%20posed%20by%20the%20recent%20Hamas%20terrorist%20attacks%20in%20Israel%20and%20their%20aftermath%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20the%20letter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Haaretz%3C%2Fem%3E%20had%20earlier%20reported%20that%20NSO%20and%20other%20Israeli%20spyware%20firms%20had%20been%20working%20with%20the%20Israeli%20government%20to%20track%20down%20missing%20hostages.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EQuoting%20experts%2C%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Intercept%20%3C%2Fem%3Enoted%20that%20the%20NSO%20was%20using%20the%20current%20crisis%20to%20make%20space%20for%20the%20group%20to%20return%20to%20the%20good%20books%20of%20Washington.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CNSO%E2%80%99s%20participation%20in%20the%20Israeli%20government%E2%80%99s%20efforts%20to%20locate%20citizens%20in%20Gaza%20seems%20to%20be%20an%20effort%20by%20the%20company%20to%20rehabilitate%20its%20image%20in%20this%20crisis%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Adam%20Shapiro%2C%20director%20of%20advocacy%20for%20Israel-Palestine%20at%20Democracy%20for%20the%20Arab%20World%20Now%2C%20a%20group%20founded%20by%20the%20slain%20journalist%20Jamal%20Khashoggi%20to%20advocate%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheintercept.com%2F2020%2F09%2F30%2Fjamal-khashoggi-dawn-saudi%2F%5C%22%3Ehuman%20rights%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0in%20the%20Middle%20East.%20%E2%80%9CBut%20alarm%20bells%20should%20be%20ringing%20that%20NSO%20Group%20has%20been%20recruited%20in%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20war%20effort.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Pegasus%20Project%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fpegasus-hacking-jamal-khashoggi-wife%5C%22%3Ehad%20traced%20the%20use%20of%20the%20Pegasus%20spyware%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20phones%20of%20close%20kin%20of%20Khashoggi%20prior%20and%20after%20his%20killing%20inside%20the%20Saudi%20consulate%20in%20Ankara.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20letter%20to%20Blinken%2C%20Dickinson%20wrote%20that%20%E2%80%9CNSO%E2%80%99s%20technology%20is%20supporting%20the%20current%20global%20fight%20against%20terrorism%20in%20any%20and%20all%20forms.%20These%20efforts%20squarely%20align%20with%20the%20Biden-Harris%20administration%E2%80%99s%20repeated%20messages%20and%20actions%20of%20support%20for%20the%20Israeli%20government%2C%20including%20from%20a%20defense%20and%20cybersecurity%20perspective.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20the%20technology%20can%20be%20%E2%80%9Cmisused%E2%80%9D%20by%20end-users%20to%20violate%20human%20rights%2C%20but%20claimed%20that%20NSO%20had%20taken%20%E2%80%9Cconcrete%20steps%20to%20address%20potential%20downstream%20human%20rights%20impacts%20of%20its%20products%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20NSO%20group%20had%20been%20in%20financial%20doldrums%20since%20it%20came%20into%20public%20spotlight%20through%20the%20Pegasus%20Project%20and%20then%20the%20blacklisting%20by%20the%20US%20Commerce%20Department.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ft.com%2Fcontent%2F24584247-0fd4-4826-bcac-f726ad17af58%3FshareType%3Dnongift%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Financial%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20had%20reported%20in%202022%20that%20the%20value%20of%20NSO%20had%20been%20deemed%20worthless%20to%20its%20private%20equity%20backers%20and%20has%20not%20received%20any%20new%20customer%20bookings%20since%20July%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699884020000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F07%2F24204013%2FIMG_4150.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Fciting-the-israel-hamas-war-nso-group-sought-urgent-meeting-with-blinken%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Quoting%20experts%2C%20The%20Intercept%20noted%20that%20the%20NSO%20was%20using%20the%20current%20crisis%20to%20make%20space%20for%20the%20group%20to%20return%20to%20the%20good%20books%20of%20Washington.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A6%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Fciting-the-israel-hamas-war-nso-group-sought-urgent-meeting-with-blinken%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Smog%20Isn%E2%80%99t%20Just%20About%20Farmers%20%E2%80%93%20We%20Breathe%20the%20Soot%20of%20Our%20Own%20Ecological%20Sins%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F12%2F14145605%2F6314806215_7aa3972351_b.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20sun%20rises%2C%20the%20grey%20lingering%20smog%20comes%20alive%20in%20north%20India.%20Over%20the%20past%20few%20days%20(and%20decades)%2C%20Delhi%20has%20become%20a%20toxic%20gas%20chamber%20signalling%20that%20all%20our%20tax%20rupees%20spent%20to%20clean%20the%20air%20have%20been%20wasted.%20AQI%20gauges%20are%20malfunctioning%20as%20air%20quality%20plummets%20beyond%20500.%20But%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20only%20our%20lungs%20but%20perhaps%20our%20brains%20that%20have%20become%20fogged.%20We%20have%20failed%20to%20see%20that%20historically%2C%20stubble%20burning%20contributes%20only%206%25%20to%20the%20pollution%2C%20yet%20the%20public%20is%20quick%20to%20make%20the%20farmers%20the%20scapegoats%2C%20and%20not%20the%20policymakers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20shouldn%E2%80%99t%20be%20too%20harsh%20on%20the%20public%2C%20as%20public%20experts%20and%20mainstream%20media%20are%20busy%20in%20political%20mudslinging%20and%20making%20the%20Punjabi%20paddy%20farmer%20India%E2%80%99s%20Public%20Enemy%20Number%20One.%20Without%20providing%20any%20real%20solutions%2C%20policymakers%20are%20keeping%20mum%20and%20deflecting%20the%20issue%20to%20the%20courts.%20Across%20state%20borders%2C%20the%20issue%20is%20highly%20politicised.%20So%2C%20it%20is%20time%20to%20examine%20the%20facts%20for%20ourselves.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20practical%20consideration%20is%20%E2%80%95%20air%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20respect%20political%20boundaries.%20Whether%20the%20factory%20or%20car%20is%20polluting%20in%20Gurugram%20or%20Noida%20or%20Bahadurgarh%2C%20people%20living%20in%20the%20NCR%20region%20have%20to%20breathe%20the%20same%20air.%20To%20get%20a%20shot%20at%20solving%20the%20problem%2C%20we%20have%20to%20consider%20the%20NCR%20region%20as%20one.%20Shifting%20factories%20from%20Delhi%20to%20the%20NCR%20regions%20of%20Haryana%20or%20UP%20is%20equally%20bad%2C%20if%20not%20worse.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMedical%20experts%20and%20researchers%20say%20that%20vehicular%20pollution%20is%20the%20main%20source%20of%20the%20toxic%20PM2.5%20pollution.%20Industries%20come%20next%2C%20followed%20by%20construction-related%20activities%20which%20raise%20dust.%20Burning%20of%20coal%20and%20other%20biomass%20also%20contributes%20to%20bad%20air.%20Mumbai%2C%20which%20is%20right%20on%20the%20sea%2C%20saw%20very%20bad%20air%20days%20without%20the%20benefit%20of%20any%20stubble%20smoke.%20Vehicles%20and%20industries%20are%20the%20major%20source%20of%20air%20pollution%2C%20not%20farmers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStubble%20burning%20is%20episodic%2C%20occuring%20in%20a%20short%20window%20of%20time%20between%20the%20kharif%20harvest%20and%20rabi%20sowing%20among%20industrial%20paddy%20farmers%2C%20and%20contributes%20about%206%25%20to%20air%20pollution.%20Stubble%20smoke%20is%20denser%20and%20visible%20to%20the%20naked%20eye%2C%20while%20vapours%20and%20NO2%20and%20carbon%20monoxide%20emitted%20from%20cars%20and%20industries%20are%20not.%20Although%20these%20non-farm%20sources%20produce%20deadlier%20smoke%2C%20the%20non-visibility%20helps%20them%20evade%20public%20attention.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20we%20look%20closely%2C%20we%20find%20that%20every%20year%2C%20long%20after%20the%20stubble%20burning%20period%20is%20over%2C%20the%20air%20quality%20in%20the%20NCR%20region%20remains%20poor%2C%20if%20not%20severe.%20What%20causes%20the%20air%20to%20remain%20bad%3F%20When%20we%20compare%20the%20pollution%20data%20not%20just%20for%20Delhi%20but%20the%20entire%20NCR%20region%2C%20it%20is%20clear%20as%20rain%20that%20it%20produces%20the%20major%20chunk%20of%20the%20pollution%20it%20breathes.%20In%20the%20summer%20and%20monsoon%20months%2C%20due%20to%20favourable%20winds%20and%20weather%2C%20pollutants%20are%20removed%20from%20our%20skies%2C%20but%20when%20winter%20comes%2C%20all%20the%20pollutants%20condense%20over%20north%20India.%20The%20retreating%20monsoon%20winds%20also%20bring%20with%20them%20the%20pollution%20and%20smoke%20from%20all%20over%20the%20northern%20Indian%20subcontinent%2C%20not%20just%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20it%20is%20very%20wrong%20to%20vilify%20farmers%20for%20air%20pollution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHaving%20shown%20that%20stubble%20smoke%20is%20responsible%20for%206%25%20of%20the%20air%20quality%20problem%2C%20we%20must%20try%20and%20find%20solutions%20for%20it.%20The%20stubble%20problem%20is%20new.%20Punjab%20and%20Haryana%20hardly%20grew%20paddy%2C%20because%20the%20local%20cuisine%20includes%20very%20little%20rice.%20Most%20rural%20households%20use%20wheat%20or%20corn%20as%20the%20staple%20cereal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPaddy%20farming%20began%20in%20Punjab%20after%20the%20Green%20Revolution%20and%20the%20development%20of%20irrigation%20systems.%20Farmers%20were%20forced%20to%20shift%20from%20native%20landraces%20and%20crops%20to%20Green%20Revolution%20paddy%20seeds.%20These%20new%20varieties%20were%20bred%20for%20higher%20uptake%20of%20agri-chemicals%20like%20urea%2C%20potash%2C%20etc%20and%20focused%20on%20producing%20more%20grains.%20The%20collateral%20damage%20was%20cattle%2C%20the%20Indian%20farmer%E2%80%99s%20best%20friend.%20The%20newer%20seeds%20had%20edible%20grains%2C%20but%20the%20straw%20was%20no%20good%20for%20fodder.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20it%20has%20no%20economic%20value%20and%20cannot%20be%20used%20as%20cattle%20feed%2C%20the%20government%20encouraged%20farmers%20to%20burn%20the%20paddy%20stubble.%20Over%20time%2C%20this%20post-harvest%20problem%20has%20picked%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20it%E2%80%99s%20the%20government%20that%20started%20this%20problem%2C%20it%20has%20the%20moral%20duty%20to%20find%20a%20solution%20for%20it%2C%20too.%20Especially%20because%20a%20large%20chunk%20of%20the%20budget%20of%20the%20national%20clean%20air%20programmes%20go%20unused.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20simple%20and%20efficient%20solution%20is%20to%20give%20farmers%20price%20support%20of%20Rs%202%2C500%20per%20acre%20to%20clear%20the%20stubble%20in%20an%20ecologically%20safe%20manner.%20An%20entire%20supply%20of%20stubble%20or%20%3Cem%3Eparali%3C%2Fem%3E-based%20raw%20material%20can%20be%20generated%20from%20paddy%20fields.%20If%20stubble%20or%20%3Cem%3Eparali%3C%2Fem%3E%20becomes%20economically%20valuable%20for%20farmers%2C%20no%20one%20would%20burn%20the%20fields.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThrough%20a%20combined%20multi-state%20action%20plan%2C%20the%20government%20can%20have%20dedicated%20mandis%20for%20stubble%20paddy%20straw%20trading.%20Like%20paddy%2C%20its%20straw%20can%20also%20have%20an%20MSP-like%20programme.%20Now%2C%20you%20may%20be%20thinking%20this%20is%20a%20subsidy%2C%20but%20it%20isn%E2%80%99t.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPaddy%20straw%20or%20stubble%20has%20multiple%20uses%20and%20the%20government%20only%20needs%20to%20regulate%20the%20market%20by%20offering%20a%20floor%20price.%20From%20the%20biochar%20industry%20(carbonised%20biomass)%20to%20mushroom%20cultivation%20and%20sustainable%20packaging%2C%20state%20governments%20can%20take%20the%20initiative%20to%20help%20organise%20this%20sector%20and%20turn%20paddy%20straw%20from%20waste%20into%20raw%20material%20for%20various%20industries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETaking%20an%20ecological%20step%20further%2C%20the%20government%20may%20have%20a%20special%20MSP%20for%20ecologically%20produced%20paddy.%20This%20would%20ensure%20that%20farmers%20are%20rewarded%20for%20growing%20basmati%20and%20other%20native%20landraces.%20The%20straw%20from%20these%20fields%20could%20help%20fill%20the%20national%20fodder%20deficit%2C%20which%20is%2010-15%25%20every%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20stubble%20problem%20is%20an%20agrarian%20problem%20which%20can%20be%20easily%20fixed%20with%20the%20right%20policy%20decisions.%20T